Quote:  A minimum of blows applied on the sheep should be aimed at. ... On good average-shearing crossbred sheep anything from fifty to sixty blows is satisfactory. <i>Ibid.</i> 65 The best way of working when crutching is to go at a good smart pace for half an hour and then have a five minutes' blow.
